wallace kirkman harrison (september 28, 1895 â€“ december 2, 1981) was an american architect.harrison started his professional career with the firm of corbett, harrison & macmurray, participating in the construction of rockefeller center. he is best known for executing large public projects in new york city and upstate, many of them a result of his long and fruitful personal relationship with nelson rockefeller, for whom he served as an adviser.